   Regulations

   Notice of Intention to Amend the Conflict of Interest Code of the
   Office of the Secretary of the Environmental Protection Agency of
   California (written submissions must be addressed to and received by
   Carol Monahan, Assistant General Counsel, Cal/EPA, 1001 I Street,
   Sacramento, CA 95814, by no later than 12:00 noon, December 21, 2001)

   Title 27: Unified Program. Title 27, Division 1, General Functions and
   Responsibilities, Subdivision 4, Sate Delegation, Chapter 1, Unified
   Hazardous Waste and Hazardous Materials Management Regulatory Program
   (Effective May 14, 1999).

   Policy Documents

   Compendium of Cal/EPA Unified Enforcement Policies

   Fact Sheets. On this page you will find 1995 and 1997 fact sheets.

   Quality Improvement Team Handbooks. Information about Senate Bill 1082
   (Calderon, Chapter 418, Statutes of 1993) directed Cal/EPA to improve
   the quality, efficiency, and cost effectiveness of our programs while
   simultaneously increasing the level of environmental protection.

